<subSubSection pageId="31" pageNumber="32" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="31.[151,1437,1348,1771]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1493,1519]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Remarks</emphasis>
. The 
<typeStatus box="[372,420,1493,1519]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">type</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Radoszkowski" authorityYear="1890" box="[458,683,1492,1518]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Spintharis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mocsaryi">
<emphasis box="[458,683,1492,1518]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Spintharis mocsaryi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingRegion box="[750,822,1493,1519]" country="Armenia" name="Ararat" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Ararat</collectingRegion>
was examined by du Buysson (1894) and re-described under the name 
<taxonomicName authority="du Buysson, 1894" authorityName="du Buysson" authorityYear="1894" box="[339,761,1528,1555]" class="Insecta" family="Masaridae" genus="Chrysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alexandri">
<emphasis box="[339,541,1528,1554]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Chrysis alexandri</emphasis>
du Buysson, 1894
</taxonomicName>
. In fact, du Buysson (1894) included in the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1761" box="[1351,1437,1528,1554]" class="Insecta" family="Masaridae" genus="Chrysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1351,1437,1528,1554]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Chrysis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
both 
<taxonomicName authority="Radoszkowski, 1889" authorityName="Radoszkowski" authorityYear="1889" box="[208,642,1564,1591]" class="Insecta" family="Masaridae" genus="Chrysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mocsaryi">
<emphasis box="[208,403,1564,1590]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Chrysis mocsaryi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Radoszkowski, O." box="[409,642,1564,1591]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" pagination="3 - 40" refId="ref24741" refString="Radoszkowski, O. (1889) Revision des armures copulatrices des males de la tribu des Chrysides. Horae Societatis Entomologicae Rossicae, 23 (1 - 2), 3 - 40, 6 pls." type="journal article" year="1889">Radoszkowski, 1889</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Radoszkowski, 1890" authorityName="Radoszkowski" authorityYear="1890" box="[696,1163,1564,1591]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Spintharis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mocsaryi">
<emphasis box="[696,921,1564,1590]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Spintharis mocsaryi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Radoszkowski, O." box="[927,1163,1564,1591]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" pagination="502 - 510" refId="ref24779" refString="Radoszkowski, O. (1890) Hymenopteres recoltes sur le mont Ararat. Horae Societatis Entomologicae Rossicae, 24, 502 - 510." type="journal article" year="1890">Radoszkowski, 1890</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, thus the latter became a secondary junior homonym. 
<bibRefCitation author="Linsenmaier, W." box="[473,688,1600,1627]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" pagination="1 - 232" refId="ref23578" refString="Linsenmaier, W. (1959) Revision der Familie Chrysididae (Hymenoptera) mit besonderer Berucksichtigung der europaischen Spezies. Mitteilungen der Schweizerischen Entomologischen Gesellschaft, 32 (1), 1 - 232." type="journal article" year="1959">Linsenmaier (1959</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Linsenmaier, W." box="[699,756,1601,1627]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" pagination="1 - 281" refId="ref23785" refString="Linsenmaier, W. (1999) Die Goldwespen Nordafrikas (Hymenoptera, Chrysididae). Entomofauna, Supplement 10, 1 - 281." type="journal article" year="1999">1999</bibRefCitation>
) identified all the specimens from East Mediterranean countries and the Middle East as 
<taxonomicName box="[471,801,1636,1663]" class="Insecta" family="Masaridae" genus="Chrysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vagans" subGenus="Spintharina">
<emphasis box="[471,557,1636,1662]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Chrysis</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[573,705,1636,1662]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Spintharina</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[722,801,1637,1662]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">vagans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, yet he did not know any real topotypic specimens from Central Asia. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="du Buysson" baseAuthorityYear="1894" box="[303,548,1672,1698]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Spintharina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alexandri">
<emphasis box="[303,548,1672,1698]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Spintharina alexandri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be easily separated from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Radoszkowski" baseAuthorityYear="1887" box="[876,1094,1672,1698]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Spintharina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vagans">
<emphasis box="[876,1094,1672,1698]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Spintharina vagans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the shape of the transversal frontal carina, simple and regularly arched (du Buysson 1894). One specimen in Radoszkowski’s collection (Rosa 
<emphasis box="[151,207,1744,1770]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">et al.</emphasis>
2015) has been erroneously considered as a 
<typeStatus box="[708,760,1745,1771]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">type</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
